From 1a59ee55dbd0d8d95f2b321a26ef478caf27538c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex Tsvetanov <alex.tsvetanov0+github@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 04:03:44 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] [clang] Deduced return type for overriding functions via
 `auto`

Implements the C++ proposal "Deduced return type for overriding functions via
`auto`": a virtual function declared with the bare `auto` placeholder together
with the `override` specifier takes its return type from the function it
overrides, fixed at the declaration. Each `return` statement must already yield
exactly that type (no implicit conversion). `auto` and the written-out type may
be mixed across the in-class declaration and an out-of-line definition; a
disagreeing written-out type is ill-formed. `decltype(auto)`/constrained
placeholders and the no-`override` case remain ill-formed ("cannot be virtual").

- SemaDeclCXX: defer the covariant-return diagnostic for an undeduced `auto`
  override; ActOnDeducedAutoOverrideReturnType fixes the return type to the
  overridden function's (or diagnoses the unsupported placeholder forms and
  multiple bases that disagree).
- SemaDecl/MergeFunctionDecl: reconcile `auto` and the written-out overridden
  type across redeclarations; diagnose a disagreeing written-out type.
- SemaStmt/BuildReturnStmt: require each return operand to already have the
  overridden type, with no implicit conversion.
- New diagnostics err_auto_override_return_mismatch /
  err_auto_override_ambiguous_return; feature-test macro
  __cpp_deduced_virtual_override_return; gated on -std=c++2c.
---
 .../clang/Basic/DiagnosticSemaKinds.td        |  6 ++
 clang/include/clang/Sema/Sema.h               | 13 ++++
 clang/lib/Frontend/InitPreprocessor.cpp       |  4 +
 clang/lib/Sema/SemaDecl.cpp                   | 39 +++++++++-
 clang/lib/Sema/SemaDeclCXX.cpp                | 74 +++++++++++++++++++
 clang/lib/Sema/SemaStmt.cpp                   | 21 ++++++
 6 files changed, 156 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

